.TH OKUAS 1 "16 June 2026" "OKU Foundation" "Usage Manual"
.SH NAME
.B okuas
\(en the minimalist Oku assembler
.SH SYNOPSIS

\fBokuas\fP
.RB [ -v ]
.RB [ -o
.IR outfile ]
.RB [ --bin ]
.RI [ file \0...]

.SH DESCRIPTION

The
.B okuas
utility is a minimalist, low-overhead assembler designed to translate human-readable 
assembly language mnemonics directly into machine code. It serves as the primary 
backend assembly phase for the
.BR okucc (1)
compiler pipeline, but is equally optimized for hand-written assembly programming.

True to the OKU philosophy,
.B okuas
does away with heavy, over-engineered abstraction layers. It provides a direct, 
predictable one-to-one mapping between assembly instructions and executable 
bytes, making it exceptionally suited for operating system development, 
bootloaders, and native freestanding software.

By default,
.B okuas
targets the native host architecture and outputs standard object files ready 
for linking or direct execution.

.SH OPTIONS

.IP \fB-o\fP\ \fIoutfile\fP
Place the primary output in
.IR outfile .
If this option is not specified, the default output name is \(oqa.out\(cq.
.IP \fB-v\fP
Display version information, supported target architectures, and OKU 
authorship credits, then exit successfully.
.IP \fB--bin\fP
Output a raw, flat binary file instead of a structured object file. In this 
mode, no file headers, section tables, or metadata segments (such as ELF headers) 
are generated. The output contains only pure machine code and data, starting 
exactly at the first byte. This is ideal for bare-metal deployment and direct 
hardware execution.

.SH INPUT FILES

The utility accepts source text files containing assembly language instructions:
.IP \fB.s\fP
Standard assembly language source files.
.IP \fB.asm\fP
Alternative extension for assembly language source files.

.SH DIAGNOSTICS

The
.B okuas
utility is designed to provide clear, human-readable error messages detailing 
exact line numbers and invalid mnemonics or malformed operands, avoiding convolved 
cryptic error codes.

